1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the analysis of a hybrid-duplex heterogeneous network, which is a type of wireless network. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the throughput of the network, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions spectral efficiency, which is a concept related to multimedia transmission. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the self-interference cancellation capability of the access points, which is a control system design problem. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not a major focus of the paper, the security implications of full-duplex communication could be relevant to this sub-category.
